  "text": "In the literature, the applications of Diaconis and Saloff-Coste's comparison method to mixing times are typically presented for the special case in which β max (M) is the second-highest eigenvalue of the transition matrix of M. In this case, it is not necessary for the flow f to be an odd flow, so the proof of Theorem 8 gives the following. [CITATION_1] Proposition 4] , which assumes that β max (M) and β max (M ′ ) correspond to the secondhighest eigenvalues of the relevant transition matrices, and that the latter is at least 1/2.",
